<br>
Imagine if back in Kunark the following zone design and spell limitations were in place.  Trak raid.  You pass the door past the portal in the basement.  It locks.  From that point on, rez sticks and rez spells don't work.  Coth don't work.  Corpse summons don't work.  The only thing you can do is fight forward, or gate/xloc out.  If raid wipes, or if all your xlocers die when raid has decided it cant push forward anymore, its summon corpse time at zone in.<br>
<br>
This would have seriously slowed down the digestion of kunark's content.  And in my opinion, it would have made the game a hella lot more fun and intense, since mistakes truly matter and focus is required.  <br>
<br>
I mean, I like vex thal.  Its a nice looking zone, and the loot is tons of fun.  Some of the encounters are pretty thrilling.  But by and large, its just a pay-off zone, and not really a huge challenge.  But what is it a pay-off for?  Well, for killing the emperor, partially.  But far and away the thing vex thall is a pay-off for is: having slogged through the incredible key grind that precedes it.  That just ain't good game design my friends.  To say, ok, you will get to go to a pretty easy zone and get phat loots if you whack a series of moles for approximately 635,000 times   ( <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smash --><img src=http://www.quellious-collective.com/emoticons/icon216.gif ALT=":smash"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) is not good game design.  It's LAZY risk v reward management on the part of verant, plain and simple.  An army of half-afk gimpologists can get to vex thall and then get the loots, as long as they are willing to suffer through a couple months of nightly unchallenging whack-a-mole.  That sucks sucks sucks.<br>
<br>
Imagine how different vex thal would be if it was a one-way dungeon, that locked down as you entered the first hallway.  (ok, so some bastid spoilers zone in and lock it down with a &quot;raid force&quot; of 4 people.  /petition, guide can boot them for being obvious jerks.)  Now rez dont work.  Coth dont work.  And if you want that Aten neck piece, you gotta fight the whole damn thing.  That's right: a two day raid.<br>
<br>
Hey, now that's heavy risk vs reward design.  But that would free up verant to design some serious zones, zones they know it will take even the top guilds several months to muscle through.  For yes, even furor uses the gimpology 101 mainstay over and over: the rez stick.<br>
<br>
Nerf the rez stick!!!!<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :ban --><img src=http://www.quellious-collective.com/emoticons/ban.gif ALT=":ban"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
